Ad Text:
6 + 12 month contract, Hybrid WFH
Baseline Security Clearance required
7 years in experience in modelling macroeconomic trends

Our client, a federal government department who is responsible in funding and regulating health care and aged care is seeking an Economic Modeller to develop economic models to quantify the changes in harmonising the care and support economy regulatory framework, based in Canberra ACT, Sydney NSW or Melbourne VIC.

Key Responsibilities of the Econometric Modeller

Ability to in measure and forecast the economic value of demand and supply;
Quantify changes for a whole of system view by using the National Accounts Framework;
Develop a comprehensive report on changes due to reform from a market and non-market perspective that includes all relevant entities in the economy;
Demonstrate a commitment to the PAS Code of Conduct and Values.

To be suitable for consideration as the Econometric Modeller, you will require:

A degree in economics, business, finance, or mathematics;
Ability to demonstrate the benefit of a regulatory reform in the care and support economy, and cost of inaction in a numerical format;
Ability to produce an impact analysis to provide insights into expected project outcomes, including a cost benefit and economic efficiencies;
Experience in building economic models that use the national accounts.

